Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.86,0:00:02.73,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A racing second hand, a shooting comet,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.73,0:00:04.93,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a pop-up doll, and broken ceramic!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.93,0:00:08.27,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Mystery-solving logic is helpful against people's dry hearts!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.27,0:00:11.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Heiji Hattori looks poised to discover Conan's real identity today!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.60,0:00:13.24,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.24,0:00:14.80,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and there's no outwitting his logic!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.80,0:00:16.93,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.19,0:01:42.59,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The old man, Ran, and I went on a trip for Sherlock Holmes fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.59,0:01:45.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}However, the car of Kanaya{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.60,0:01:48.97,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}this trip's director and owner of the Mycroft Lodge,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.97,0:01:51.80,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}fell over a cliff and exploded!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.28,0:02:01.45,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Moreover, having been isolated from the outside world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.45,0:02:05.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}we shut ourselves in the lodge to prevent any further casualties,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.12,0:02:07.98,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but Ayako{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}, who claimed to know the identity of the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.32,0:02:11.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}died in an explosion in the garage!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.39,0:02:14.53,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Was the owner responsible?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.53,0:02:17.53,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Or was it one of the five other guests
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.53,0:02:19.93,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}excluding us three and Heiji Hattori?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.93,0:02:25.20,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Suddenly, Fujisawa{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10} was attacked by someone with an ice pick!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.61,0:02:38.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who would do such a thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.84,0:02:40.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.12,0:02:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He faked his death during the first incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.92,0:02:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,hid somewhere inside this lodge,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.29,0:02:48.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,burned Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to death in the garage,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.56,0:02:51.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then attacked Fujisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with an ice pick
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.90,0:02:54.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and escaped out that window!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.90,0:02:58.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it! Why would the owner want to kill me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.40,0:03:01.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I even helped him with the book he published!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.97,0:03:03.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Book?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.21,0:03:06.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Holmes book he published last year with his own money.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.58,0:03:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe the title was\N"The Disparagement of Irene Adler."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.38,0:03:11.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Irene Adler?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.19,0:03:16.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, Ran! We're going after the owner!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.79,0:03:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.99,0:03:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forget about it. There's no point.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.99,0:03:24.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd never find the killer by looking out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.53,0:03:25.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.80,0:03:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a closer look at this chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.00,0:03:30.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See how it's unnaturally placed at the narrow end?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.87,0:03:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's proof that the killer quickly pushed it under
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.00,0:03:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after breaking the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.47,0:03:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right! There are pieces of glass stuck in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.11,0:03:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer must have used this chair!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.95,0:03:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that only proves the killer used the chair to—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.68,0:03:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot! Who would bother putting a chair back
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.19,0:03:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after smashing a window to escape through it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.39,0:03:53.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer probably held the chair with bare hands
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.09,0:03:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when they broke the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.99,0:03:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was too dark to remove the fingerprints,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.53,0:04:00.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the killer put the chair back under the table—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.87,0:04:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we wouldn't notice and so they could wipe the fingerprints off
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.30,0:04:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when no one was looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.97,0:04:10.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the lights came back on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.14,0:04:13.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, we were the only ones in the room then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.78,0:04:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.38,0:04:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now do you see that the owner didn't do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and that the killer is in this very room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.59,0:04:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maid. You said a fuse had blown
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.13,0:04:31.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when the lights went out, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.80,0:04:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! When I tried to plug in the coffee maker,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.60,0:04:37.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it suddenly sparked!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.54,0:04:41.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was this outlet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.34,0:04:44.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a thin wire wrapped around the plug
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.54,0:04:48.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so that it would cause a short if someone were to plug it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.18,0:04:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But where did the killer get this wire?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.95,0:04:53.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet it was this!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.62,0:04:57.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wire attached to the top of this coffee pack!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.62,0:05:01.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The width and length do match perfectly...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.63,0:05:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who opened the packs?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.46,0:05:06.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kawatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Togano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.97,0:05:10.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now it's clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.04,0:05:13.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the killer, Kawatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.97,0:05:16.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.78,0:05:20.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were three other people in the kitchen besides me—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.08,0:05:21.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.08,0:05:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All three of those people have alibis for the first incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.82,0:05:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You most likely took a wire off a pack when no one was looking,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.16,0:05:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wrapped it around the plug, and then returned to the living room
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.66,0:05:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to wait for the lights to go out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.70,0:05:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, in the darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.60,0:05:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you attacked Fujisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with an ice pick
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.17,0:05:43.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that you carried in here with some ice—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.17,0:05:46.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,using the flame from his lighter to find him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.61,0:05:50.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, some unexpected obstacles caused you to fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.18,0:05:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.48,0:05:57.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but something's not quite right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.38,0:05:58.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.72,0:05:59.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.42,0:06:02.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The third incident in which Fujisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was attacked
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.99,0:06:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is different than the first two
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.19,0:06:08.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in that the culprit plainly left evidence behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.06,0:06:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps this third incident wasn't part of the killer's plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.13,0:06:15.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.77,0:06:20.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm just a kid, so what would I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.97,0:06:23.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't pay any attention to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.68,0:06:26.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He just loves to play detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.65,0:06:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.35,0:06:32.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's something really strange about this kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.85,0:06:37.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He isn't playing detective! He's really analyzing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.16,0:06:40.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His voice and body are different, but he's almost just like Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:43.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kudo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.90,0:06:47.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah! When Kudo showed up during that previous incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.17,0:06:49.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}that kid disappeared somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.60,0:06:53.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And then when Kudo disappeared, he just popped up again...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.47,0:06:57.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could he really be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.35,0:07:04.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't it strange, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.72,0:07:07.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Kawatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really is the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.82,0:07:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,how did he set the garage on fire during the second incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.06,0:07:14.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And during the first incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.29,0:07:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the owner's car sped up before it went over the cliff!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.13,0:07:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.87,0:07:22.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.37,0:07:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got almost all of the second incident solved,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.47,0:07:26.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the first incident makes no sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.77,0:07:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? You know how they set the garage on fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.31,0:07:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.78,0:07:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, what I don't understand about the first incident
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.31,0:07:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,are the following four points.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.01,0:07:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why we didn't see the owner for almost an entire day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.52,0:07:42.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why the car suddenly sped up...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.25,0:07:45.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The odd sound coming from inside the car
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.42,0:07:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the blanket on the dashboard...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.09,0:07:51.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then one more mystery appeared when we came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.06,0:07:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The owner was holding the steering wheel tightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.80,0:07:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The car was on a bumpy road, but his body never slumped.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.60,0:08:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means by the time he was placed in the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.81,0:08:05.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he was long dead and rigor mortis had set in!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.28,0:08:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rigor mortis?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.38,0:08:13.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A body usually begins to stiffen 30 minutes to 2 hours after death,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.49,0:08:16.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and 9 to 12 hours later, the body becomes completely stiff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.86,0:08:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thirty hours after that, under the best circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.63,0:08:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the body loosens up again and approximately 70 hours later
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.19,0:08:25.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.30,0:08:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we assume the owner was completely stiff
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.87,0:08:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when he was placed in the car at 3:30 AM,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.54,0:08:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then he was killed between 3:30 and 6:30 PM the previous day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.91,0:08:39.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, sometime before dinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.44,0:08:41.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but what I don't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.85,0:08:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is why they had to put him in the car so early...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.22,0:08:47.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe to make it look like a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.99,0:08:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My guess is that they killed the owner before dinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.12,0:08:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,put him in the car, had him sit with his hands on the wheel,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.09,0:08:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,waited for him to stiffen, then went to the garage after dinner
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.33,0:08:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and sent the car on its way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.40,0:09:00.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.70,0:09:04.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer was one of you who left after dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.74,0:09:07.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why did the car speed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.61,0:09:10.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dead person couldn't possibly have done that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.58,0:09:11.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A dead person?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.51,0:09:15.14,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could the killer's trick be—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.85,0:09:18.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If so, then only that person could've done it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.68,0:09:20.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but there's still no proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.62,0:09:21.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.75,0:09:25.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She did say that Ayako{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was loitering in the hall in the afternoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.29,0:09:30.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If she had actually seen something in that person's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.57,0:09:34.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.97,0:09:35.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.93,0:09:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know the killer's identity!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.94,0:09:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the killer is you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.41,0:09:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fortune-teller Maria Toda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.91,0:09:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.48,0:09:50.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must have used hypnosis to make the owner drive the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.88,0:09:52.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.15,0:09:55.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can't wait to use a sleeping dart on him...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.59,0:09:59.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But it's all over if he catches me during my explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.59,0:10:01.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say! What would happen to the rigor mortis
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.26,0:10:03.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if the temperature went up?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.26,0:10:05.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would it start sooner?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.40,0:10:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so, then you know who did it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.17,0:10:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't the slightest idea. I'm pretty dumb, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.71,0:10:15.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.01,0:10:18.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He knows all right, he's just trying to make me explain it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.41,0:10:19.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Alright, in that case!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.75,0:10:22.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll just be going to the bathroom now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.95,0:10:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. Then I will, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.52,0:10:27.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where'd he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.59,0:10:32.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you get serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.36,0:10:35.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a fortune-teller, not a magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.59,0:10:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough of this farce, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.83,0:10:39.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.16,0:10:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just figured out who the killer is, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.34,0:10:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.80,0:10:46.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person behind all three incidents at this lodge... was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.47,0:11:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.24,0:11:05.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person behind all three incidents at this lodge...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.67,0:11:07.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.34,0:11:09.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.08,0:11:11.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.01,0:11:14.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man in a cold sweat behind you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.15,0:11:16.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...you, Togano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.92,0:11:21.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.22,0:11:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was here in the living room hours before the car even took off!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.36,0:11:29.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when Ayako was killed, I was with everyone else!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.03,0:11:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right, you moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.00,0:11:35.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, man! I hope he didn't wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.27,0:11:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop that, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.04,0:11:40.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you mock me with your fancy Kansai dialect!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.71,0:11:46.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And besides, you were with us too when the car started moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.51,0:11:50.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could Togano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} possibly have started the car?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.29,0:11:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right, it certainly appears impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.39,0:11:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if he were to utilize the rigor mortis
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.96,0:12:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a certain function of the car, it would become possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.06,0:12:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The trick goes like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.73,0:12:06.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit killed the owner almost exactly one day ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.40,0:12:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,sat him in the car seat, and stuck his foot on the brake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.84,0:12:13.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rigor mortis would occur half a day later,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.07,0:12:15.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the brakes would have kept the car motionless
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.74,0:12:19.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,even if the engine was running and in drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.41,0:12:22.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before dinner last night, the killer opened the garage
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.75,0:12:27.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then waited in the living room for the foot on the brake to loosen up
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.42,0:12:29.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and cause the car to start moving...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.19,0:12:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.76,0:12:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rigor mortis doesn't go away
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.99,0:12:36.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,until at least 40 hours after death!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.70,0:12:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You even said so yourself—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.17,0:12:41.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if the outside temperature increases?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.50,0:12:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the temperature around the body was about 35°C,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.41,0:12:48.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the rigor mortis and rate of loosening up would speed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.51,0:12:52.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so it would start to go away after only 24 to 30 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.15,0:12:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was after 10:00 PM two nights ago that the owner disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.39,0:13:00.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he had been killed shortly afterward...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.36,0:13:03.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The car started moving approximately 29 hours later
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.06,0:13:05.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,—before 3:30 this morning—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.53,0:13:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which was just about the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.30,0:13:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hissing sound we heard inside the car
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.53,0:13:12.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wasn't the air conditioner—it was the heater!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.00,0:13:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had it been the AC,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.17,0:13:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,water drops would have fallen by the front tires.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.81,0:13:21.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why you were checking around the tire tracks?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.91,0:13:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:26.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naturally, there were no water marks to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.78,0:13:28.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that trick would be easy to see through
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.92,0:13:30.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,by checking the body...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.65,0:13:35.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the killer sent the owner over the cliff in the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.29,0:13:37.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To make the body unrecoverable
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.03,0:13:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we couldn't check the state of rigor mortis!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.36,0:13:43.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why did the car speed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.70,0:13:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably because his foot slipped off the brake pedal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.60,0:13:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as the car bumped around.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.77,0:13:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the blanket on the dashboard
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.88,0:13:56.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was there to conceal the heater indicator
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.38,0:13:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from people who got near the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.45,0:14:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.95,0:14:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So by witnessing the car with someone else in the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.32,0:14:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...they would have an airtight alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.53,0:14:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the reason Togano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} kept Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in the living room
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.20,0:14:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was because he wanted someone who would witness the car with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.40,0:14:22.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.07,0:14:25.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the only person who could have done such a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.21,0:14:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was Togano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.81,0:14:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.08,0:14:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your theory almost sounds like it's straight out of a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.08,0:14:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too bad you have no evidence to prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.55,0:14:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as I've said before, when the fire erupted in the garage,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.36,0:14:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in here with everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.09,0:14:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how you look at it, there's no way
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.83,0:14:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could have set the fire exactly when Ayako happened to go in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.03,0:14:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, but it would still be easy enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.84,0:14:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All you had to do was tell her
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.54,0:15:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that the first-edition Holmes book was hidden beneath the back seat
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.51,0:15:02.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of the car in the garage!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.21,0:15:07.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The first-edition book? What's that have to do with anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.12,0:15:08.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.52,0:15:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, the car in the garage was drained of its gasoline
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.82,0:15:14.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and its battery removed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.66,0:15:16.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She wanted to look for the book, but with the car lights unusable
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.12,0:15:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the back seat would have been pitch black.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.40,0:15:22.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What would you have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.06,0:15:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were pitch dark, I'd have to use a lighter or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.20,0:15:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! A lighter!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.57,0:15:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} used a lighter to look for the book!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.24,0:15:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flame ignited the gasoline that had leaked from the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.91,0:15:41.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she was the one who started the fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.68,0:15:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she was an important witness from the first incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.25,0:15:50.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were four other witnesses besides her!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.26,0:15:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was no need to keep her alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.03,0:15:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But aren't Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Togano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} lovers?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.20,0:15:58.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.70,0:16:01.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because she figured out his rigor mortis trick
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.77,0:16:05.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and found evidence that he was the one responsible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.04,0:16:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You all remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.38,0:16:10.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} declared she knew who the killer was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.18,0:16:13.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hearing that, Togano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} grew flustered
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.08,0:16:16.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and pretended to follow her to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.58,0:16:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then told her about the first-edition book
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.59,0:16:20.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and lured her into the trap in the garage!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.86,0:16:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.39,0:16:25.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Togano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the only one alone with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.73,0:16:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why she changed her attitude after leaving the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.76,0:16:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he certainly was clever to come up with that garage trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.20,0:16:40.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. That trap had been prepared in advance for a certain person...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.21,0:16:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer lucked out because Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had a lighter,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.98,0:16:46.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,just as that other person would have had!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.18,0:16:52.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The trap in the garage was really meant to kill Fujisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.66,0:16:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.59,0:16:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That card that was stuck in your door...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.03,0:17:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer intended to lure you into the garage and murder you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.03,0:17:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But things didn't go according to plan
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.80,0:17:09.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the garage trap wound up killing Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.70,0:17:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He quickly devised a plan to cause a blackout
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.87,0:17:13.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,by fiddling with the outlet
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.51,0:17:16.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then attacked Fujisawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with an ice pick!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.61,0:17:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So that's why there was so much evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.78,0:17:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after the third incident...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.05,0:17:24.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Togano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was in the kitchen at the time—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.62,0:17:27.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he could've very easily fiddled with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.86,0:17:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the only person
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.06,0:17:34.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who could've pulled off all three incidents...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.40,0:17:36.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...was Togano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.00,0:17:38.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then show us your proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.33,0:17:43.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're going to make such accusations, then surely you have proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.34,0:17:45.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? You mean you didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.57,0:17:49.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw a certain something in your room
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.84,0:17:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,yesterday afternoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.35,0:17:54.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter what she saw! She can't talk now—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.68,0:17:56.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Question #1.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.22,0:17:58.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Which hand does Holmes write with?"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.79,0:17:59.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Question #2.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.85,0:18:02.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"What is the name of Dr. Watson's wife?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.42,0:18:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.36,0:18:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, my. Have you forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.36,0:18:10.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you take the Holmes Cult Test of 1000 Questions too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.37,0:18:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Question #241.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.57,0:18:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"What did Holmes' letter written in the 'Dancing Men' code
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.94,0:18:19.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,say to the killer?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.61,0:18:23.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I remember that question very well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:26.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The answer is, "Come here at once!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.81,0:18:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That question wasn't on the test...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.82,0:18:33.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was only that one question about "The Dancing Men"!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.59,0:18:37.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Write down the entire 'Dancing Men' code as it appeared!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.76,0:18:38.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.89,0:18:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That question was so hard it would be impossible to forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.43,0:18:46.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it a little strange that you don't remember it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.47,0:18:48.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.10,0:18:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to your room
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.41,0:18:53.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was to copy your test answers!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.07,0:18:56.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you weren't in your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.41,0:18:58.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had probably gone to the garage
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.25,0:19:00.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to check the state of the owner's rigor mortis!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.58,0:19:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what Ayako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} saw was—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.92,0:19:08.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. A completely blank test with no answers written at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.79,0:19:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason he didn't write anything down
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.26,0:19:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was because there would be no point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.13,0:19:17.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.03,0:19:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you knew that the owner wouldn't be grading the tests
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.37,0:19:22.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because he was no longer alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.91,0:19:25.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're going to claim this is all nonsense,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.71,0:19:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then would you kindly show us your test?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.18,0:19:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.28,0:19:33.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.71,0:19:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.78,0:19:40.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speak up! Why did you want me and the owner dead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.39,0:19:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The Disparagement of Irene Adler."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.89,0:19:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His motive was most likely the book you helped the owner write.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.66,0:19:50.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.87,0:19:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Irene? The actress who outwitted Holmes in one of the stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.67,0:19:58.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. But the owner's book was mostly about
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.84,0:20:01.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Holmes' failure as a detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.21,0:20:02.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.18,0:20:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Togano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} felt that the book insulted Holmes, so he—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.35,0:20:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.12,0:20:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Irene was the only woman Sherlock admired.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.92,0:20:16.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't possibly see such a woman ridiculing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.89,0:20:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't allow it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.50,0:20:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I absolutely couldn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.71,0:20:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was incredible, Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.54,0:20:37.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what I'd expect from the great western detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.51,0:20:39.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Uh oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.65,0:20:41.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.22,0:20:45.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A case like this is like a walk in the park for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.55,0:20:49.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Looks like I made it through this without having my cover blown...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.22,0:20:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.73,0:20:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.26,0:20:56.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm right here, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.50,0:20:57.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.53,0:21:00.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're Kudo, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.07,0:21:05.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? I'm just a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.47,0:21:09.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your fake Kansai dialect was pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.01,0:21:12.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! So this is the gizmo you used to imitate my voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.58,0:21:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw you using it in the corner of my eye!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.22,0:21:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At what point?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.79,0:21:21.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It would become possible."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.19,0:21:23.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You talk a little strangely,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.22,0:21:25.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but from your tone and the way you set up your theories
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.36,0:21:27.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you're definitely Shin'ichi Kudo!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.13,0:21:29.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? Look at me! I'm just a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.83,0:21:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fine, have it your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.03,0:21:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, check this out! You'll never guess!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.20,0:21:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.57,0:21:41.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.38,0:23:10.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So their drug shrunk you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.65,0:23:13.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and now you're living with your girlfriend
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.18,0:23:16.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to find out about their organization?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.72,0:23:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's not my girlfriend. She's a pain in the ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.13,0:23:24.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two sure are getting along well!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.83,0:23:26.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.00,0:23:30.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, wanna hear what Kudo once said about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.40,0:23:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said you're so annoying he can't stand you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.47,0:23:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Annoying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.14,0:23:40.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.34,0:23:42.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's what you get for putting me to sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.29,0:23:56.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.85,0:23:58.56,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Someone cut this!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.56,0:24:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone tried to kill Hiroshi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} in fake accidents!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.15,0:24:15.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.12,0:24:20.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Traffic Mirror
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.45,0:24:22.19,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, it's a super-popular series!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.19,0:24:24.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A big role for the Detective Boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.31,0:24:25.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Not again...
